<br>
My journeys continued through the pitch black of the nightworld Norrath for many days until I reached a great chasm.  It was there that I stumbled across a body in what presumably was snow.  Bending to my knees, I groped for the poor fellow shaking him to see if there was any chance for life.<br>
<br>
&quot;I am Viraan &quot;the blind&quot;&quot; I said, &quot;I have come to help&quot;  I felt a faint pulse on the cold flesh of his neck.<br>
The prone figure responded &quot;beat it buddy....&quot;.  I knew he must be in a state of delirium given the cold so I reached for my pack and my supply of healing potions and poured some in his mouth.<br>
<br>
&quot;What are you doing?&quot; he screamed.  &quot;Why in the name of Ro are you pouring short beer on my arse?&quot;<br>
I cursed the confused merchant who had sold me the potions, realizing that I had once again been duped.<br>
<br>
It was at this point when I heard giant footsteps approaching at an alarming rate.<br>
&quot;So...thought you could feign death, eh?&quot; boomed a giant voice.<br>
<br>
The previously prone figure whirred into action, and I could hear him pad off at top speed.  There was a sharp crack, followed by a deathly silence.<br>
<br>
--You gain faction with the Kromrif Death Squad.<br>
<br>
&quot;Such is the fate of those who defy the Kromrif&quot;, bellowed the voice.<br>
<br>
NEXT WEEK:  Viraan meets the Kromrif King<br>
<br>
Viraan says &quot;Take this gift of fine armor as a token of my servitude&quot;<br>
Kromrif King &quot;Um....that is a stack of brownie parts.... good enough!&quot;<br>
