<br>
I have come to understand that my equipment is sorely lacking.  To determine what attire is appropriate for someone of my stature, I attempted to consult with some lore-masters in the fair city of Kelethin.  After I ascended upwards into its treetop walkways, I found that these elves did not speak proper elvish, but instead a strange bird-like language make up of only squawks and chirps.<br>
<br>
After sitting for a while listening to their beautiful but unintelligible tongue I was rudely interrupted by some oaf who demanded that I either pull an aviak or get out of the penthouse.  Confused, I descended to the ground.<br>
<br>
Later, I ran into a helpful person who advised me to kill Dyllin Starshine, a notorious bandit, to obtain the Testament of Vanear.<br>
<br>
A goal in sight (so to speak), I made my way to Highpass Hold.<br>
<br>
It was to be an arduous camp, I was told, fraught with claim-jumpers and the risk that the nearby bandits would come to Dyllin’s aid.  I sat on the planks where the bandit was to appear and began my long wait.<br>
<br>
The warning that other people may contest my right to the bounty on Starshine proved true.  Over the hours, my keen ears picked out footsteps on the planking, but when I stood and threatened them with my weapon, they always backed off, respecting my camp.<br>
<br>
Finally, after several hours, I heard some hobnailed boots treading the boards near me.<br>
<br>
“Dyllin Starshine?” I demanded, “Have you come at last to face your doom?”<br>
<br>
“What are you doing?” asked a gruff voice.  I recognized it as dwarven.<br>
<br>
Realizing that this was not my quarry, I moved swiftly to claim my right to the spot.<br>
<br>
“This is my camp!  Be off with you!”<br>
<br>
Previous interlopers had backed off quickly.  This one seemed persistent.<br>
<br>
“What are you talking about?” he asked.<br>
<br>
“If you want this camp, you’ll have to wait your turn!”<br>
<br>
“This is the boat form Freeport to Butcher Block.”<br>
<br>
I briefly considered his words, but luckily I had been warned in advance to expect people to try and steal my kill.<br>
<br>
“Away with you!” I screamed shrilly, “Or you’ll taste the sting of THIS!”<br>
<br>
I whipped out my weapon and brandished it in what I hoped was a threatening manner.<br>
<br>
“That is an iron ration.”<br>
<br>
